      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2.",
      "rationale": "Model form uncertainty assessment not required at MRL 2. The power-law hemolysis model (Giersiepen et al.) is the accepted industry standard for CFD hemolysis prediction and its use is consistent with FDA guidance."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All model inputs documented with sources; uncertain inputs assigned probability distributions informed by literature or measurement data.",
      "rationale": "All 13 model inputs documented including blood viscosity, density, power-law exponents, inlet velocity profile, and rotational speed. Uncertain inputs assigned distributions: blood viscosity modeled as normal (mean 3.5 mPa·s, CV 8%), inlet flow rate as uniform ±3% of nominal. Monte Carlo UQ propagated these distributions through 2000 model evaluations to yield 95% confidence intervals on RH. All input distributions traceable to published hematology literature."
    },
